lastTick(Spec).notice: lastTick calculates the previous datetime that a spec "ticks", starting from the current block timestamp. This is gas-intensive and therefore should only be called off-chain.

matches(Spec,uint256).notice: matches evaluates whether or not a spec "ticks" at a given timestamp

nextTick(Spec).notice: nextTick calculates the next datetime that a spec "ticks", starting from the current block timestamp. This is gas-intensive and therefore should only be called off-chain.

toCronString(Spec).notice: toCronString converts a cron spec to a human-readable cron string. This is gas-intensive and therefore should only be called off-chain.

toEncodedSpec(string).notice: toEncodedSpec converts a cron string to an abi-encoded spec. This is gas-intensive and therefore should only be called off-chain.

toSpec(string).notice: toSpec converts a cron string to a spec struct. This is gas-intensive and therefore should only be called off-chain.
